<h3>Area of a Triangle</h3>
<p>There are multiple different equations for calculating the area of a tri=
angle, dependent on what information is known. Likely the most commonly kno=
wn equation for calculating the area of a triangle involves its base, <b>b<=
/b>, and height, <b>h</b>. The "base" refers to any side of the triangle wh=
ere the height is represented by the length of the line segment drawn from =
the vertex opposite the base, to a point on the base that forms a perpendic=
ular.</p>

